.TH OPTIMIZE 1 "July 2026" "1.0.0" "optimize manual"
.SH NAME
optimize \- Build optimized Debian/Ubuntu packages from source
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B optimize
[\fB-c\fR|\fB--cflags\fR \fIFLAGS\fR]
[\fB-x\fR|\fB--cxxflags\fR \fIFLAGS\fR]
[\fB-j\fR|\fB--jobs\fR \fIN\fR]
.I package-name
.PP
.B optimize
[\fB-h\fR|\fB--help\fR]
.PP
.B optimize
[\fB-V\fR|\fB--version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B optimize
is a modern, robust replacement for apt-build. It automates the process of downloading, compiling, and optimizing Debian and Ubuntu packages from source in a clean, isolated chroot environment using \fBsbuild\fR.
.PP
It ensures packages are built with hardware-specific optimizations (such as \fB-O3\fR and \fB-march=native\fR) safely, without risking the stability of your host system.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-c\fR, \fB--cflags\fR \fIFLAGS\fR
Set custom C compiler flags. Default: \fI-O3 -march=native -pipe\fR.
.TP
\fB-x\fR, \fB--cxxflags\fR \fIFLAGS\fR
Set custom C++ compiler flags. Default: \fI-O3 -march=native -pipe\fR.
.TP
\fB-j\fR, \fB--jobs\fR \fIN\fR
Specify the number of parallel build jobs. Defaults to automatic detection via \fBnproc\fR.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Show the help message and exit.
.TP
\fB-V\fR, \fB--version\fR
Show version information and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B optimize
automatically configures the build environment by injecting variables into the \fB~/.sbuildrc\fR file. It relies on standard Debian build variables like \fBDEB_CFLAGS_APPEND\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR apt-get (8),
.BR sbuild (1),
.BR schroot (1)
